$ROOT_QUERY.business({\"encid\":\"woTZpX.full: 5 star service. We got seated at a table, but requested a booth. We were quickly seated at a booth,and it was roomy and comfortable. Appetizers were delicious- I got west coast oysters, a delicious seafood (tuna, salmon, and hamachi) roll, and they also brought sourdough bread and fresh pretzel rolls to the table. I appreciated the sourdough bread as I have recently transitioned to gluten free, and with a healthy smear of butter, my stomach was good to go. I had the Chilean sea bass for my main- and wished it came with a different side, like the risotto. However everything I had was delicious. I am going back for restaurant week! The last bit that really did it for me was one of the restaurant managers coming over to our table- introducing himself- and talking whiskey with me. I ordered a whisky sour (it was pretty good) but this manager (Bob is his first name) made me a SPECIAL whisky sour that was absolutely divine. Amazing customer service, great food, and next time I am trying the dessert menu.

I made reservations here for my husband's birthday, our first time dining here. Beautiful place! Service was amazing, food was delicious! It is a bit pricey but it was worth it. 
The only complaint I have is, we got seated what seemed to be a private dining room area. All the windows were covered with curtains so you can't see the main dining area or the bar. So I felt like we were just closed in and really didn't get to experience the restaurant's environment. I wish they would of ask us if it's okay for us to be seated inside there. 
Overall it is a nice place BUT pricey. We wouldn't come here all the time.

I have been to Ocean Prime many times and this visit did not disappoint. The service was fantastic from the time we walked in until the time we left.

I enjoyed my cocktail, salmon with sticky rice, and asparagus with hollandaise sauce. I wanted to take just half a star away because I asked for the hollandaise sauce to go with my leftover asparagus but my to go bag did not include it.

It should actually be illegal for food to be this good. 
I can't recommend it enough. The lobster bisque, the sea food tower, the steak.... Everything was better than the next thing we ordered. We must have caught them on a busy night where our service wasn't great but it still didn't matter- the food was that good. 
My only issue is that it's so stupid-expensive that it's just not something we can do all of the time. I wish they would lower their pricing a little bit so we could go more often but for a splurge kind of date night, it's perfect.

Visited Ocean Prime to kick off center city district restaurant week. It was not busy at all ( could be due to the Eagles game). Service was great! No long waits! I usually get Steak but decided to try the Teriyaki Salmon and it was a great choice. My cocktail of choice was the berries and bubbles which is a whole moment with bubbles and smoke. Music played in the background and was not too loud. Great choice for a date night.

Gorgeous interior and fantastic meal.  We were originally sat directly in front of the glass wall that shows the kitchen/drop area.  It's nice to view but I don't want to sit there, especially not for my birthday.  We spoke with the server and we were moved to a booth.  Much better. 

The bread was slapping. I almost ignored the pretzels but glad I tried it because when that salt mixed with the whipped butter oooo weee.  We got 2 baskets because we fasted for 20 hours and also because we're greedy.

We started with crème brûlée (hey, I said it's my birthday), drinks, Parmesan fries and the shrimp sauté.  I got Bubbling Berries as my drink and my partner got the pineapple something or another.  It had St Germain in it and it was definitely not his style. My drink was amazing so I had two. The Parmesan fries were delicious.  Nice and thick cut.  If you're gonna pay for gourmet fries these are it.  Simple and delicious.  That shrimp sautée was tasty as well. Large shrimp and the toast points that come with it are top notch.  Premium, flaky sliced bread with melted cheese on top. The sauce at the bottom of the dish is heavenly.  We slid our bread all through there and were not disappointed. 

For dinner we got twin lobster tails, blacked snapper, jalapeño au gratin, and truffle Mac and cheese.  I'm so glad the lobster came with a few asparagus pieces since we didn't bother ordering any veggies today.  I mean, we didn't eat them, but they definitely made us look more mature than our order let on. Lobster was delicious, the butter warmer was a nice touch.  The Blacked catfish honestly looks more delicious than it really is.  We should've gotten four lobster tails. Both side dishes were amazing.

We finished off our meal with more creme brûlée cause I told y'all it's my birthday.  Honestly there's is the best I've had.  It's smooth, creamy, and they have the thickest brûlée layer I've had anyplace else.  I'll be going back for more.  $300 (before tip)for this yummy dinner; vibes=priceless.

This place was nice , but I did expect for it to be bigger! We went yesterday which was Valentine's Day and I must say there was kids running around, which made me quite surprised! However our waiter Kimani was nice and professional plus also very polite and knew when we needed a refill without even having to ask! He asked the most important questions to make our visit a success! The only thing that bothered me when it came to the food I did not like how the food took a little longer than I would had anticipated but I'm am fully aware that it was so many people there this night that was ordering so I do understand how that could've created a delay. But all in all this is a very good place! The food , the service & they had an AMAZINGGGGG playlist!

This place was recommended by my sister who is a Philadelphia foodie and it did not disappoint. However, make sure your wallet is ready! I had oysters and a crab cake along with an old fashioned. Everything was good. I think the best part to me was the ambiance, very intimate and classy and the staff...from the front door to the management were super pleasant. Highly recommended!

While visiting Philly for the weekend my boyfriend and I decided on this establishment. He eats steak I don't but he said let's try here. We started off with drinks I had the Berries and Bubbles nothing special just that it was bubbly. So when dinner arrived everything went down hill. As I stated my boyfriend wanted steak his steak came out warm. He also ordered a bake potatoe that was cold inside and requested no bacon. It also had bacon on it. I had Salmon which came out warm. The waitress apologized and bought him out mash potatoes which actually was the hottest dish on the table. The manager came over apologized and informed he would do something for our bill. It seems as if the entire side we were sitting on was having issues as I noticed the manager speaking with numerous table. Anyhow all said and done he took one drink off the bill and that's it. Over $200 bill for food we didn't even eat. Needless to say I won't be going back here.  We travel a lot and love a great meal so paying is not a problem but for what we endured we ended up going to our hotel and ordering more food because honestly we were still hungary

My partner and I started out splitting the surf and turf appetizer (scallops and short rib). Delicious.

I started with a Berries and Bubbles cocktail (tart and fruity) and my partner got the cucumber gimlet. I preferred the gimlet so I switched to that for my second cocktail.

Partner had the NY strip and lobster bisque. Both were good. The lobster bisque didn't have much lobster to bisque ratio but the bisque was uniquely seasoned (we couldn't put our finger on what was special about it but we both agreed it was tasty!).

I had the king salmon. Large portion of salmon for sure (probably close to 8 oz.). Just a few gnocchi with it but the couple pieces of lobster were more significant than I expected.

We shared a butter cake for dessert. It was good but honestly any warm freshly baked cake, ice cream and berries are good. It wasn't super special.

Maybe slightly overpriced compared to other fine dining places we've been in DC and Philadelphia.

I will keep this one short and sweet.  I have eaten here numerous times.  The atmosphere is always welcoming, the service is always spot on, and the food is always exceptional.  I ate here this past Monday night and had the scallop and short rib appetizer for starters.  It may be the best appetizer I have ever had.  Perfect!  For my entree, I had the twin lobster tails with asparagus and a side of jalapeno au gratin potatoes.  Again, all Perfect.  The lobster was plump and tender, the asparagus was delicious, and the potatoes were beyond compare.  I could eat a bowl just of those potatoes, they are so dang good!  Did not have room for the dessert!  I promise, you can't go wrong here!
Loved the whole experience from start to finish! Worth every penny . Service, food .ambiance will go again

This special occasion was a belated birthday celebration and the first dinner outing since 2019. As a professional of the hospitality industry since 1991, it's heartbreaking that so many businesses no longer exist or the quality of service, food and experience have changed. 

I have ALWAYS loved Ocean Prime for being consistent with exceptional cuisines that accommodate dietary restrictions. The unique personalized and compassionate customer service demonstrates true teamwork. The ambiance encompassed comfortable seating and a relaxing slightly pleasant musical play list if you pause to just embrace this lovely experience. 

I am looking forward to future reservations. Thank you Queen, Isabel, Adam, and Manager for providing a wonderful evening and an escape from my daily routine.

Service, Mario was an amazing waiter, quick, helpful and extremely personal. 

Absolutely incredible food & service. Seafood and steaks were all cooked to perfection. Mario, our server, provided quick and efficient service throughout our night. The ambiance is suitable for a nice night out with your significant other.

Jesus was our waiter and made our experience really wonderful. He was friendly and efficient. We all got the chilled crab appetizer that was phenomenal. No one was disappointed. My table mates got the surf and surf . It was scallops and lobster tail served over lemon mashed potatoes. The scallops were cooked perfectly and the lobster portion generous. My son got the Salmon teriyaki served over mashed potatoes, the salmon  was flaky and cooked just right, the serving generous. We got the miso broccoli and we found it to be a little too salty. I got the Chilean sea bass. The fish was delicious however I am from Columbus and the Cameron Mitchell restaurant there cooks it differently and better. It had a sauce and Prime didn't have it.

Had a fantastic meal, tuna was cooked perfectly, and the lobster linguine was awesome. The garlic shrimp appetizer was good, and the three pieces of cheesy bread to dip in the sauce for fantastic. For dessert the butter cake was unbelievable. Can't even explain how good the service was. Had people waiting on us hand and foot lol.

Always a good go-to for date night or special occasion. Of course it's pricey but so worth it. There's valet right out front so you don't have to worry about parking. The steaks are such good cuts and basically melts in your mouth. Service is always top notch. Haven't had a bad experience yet. The wait staff are also friendly and ready to give you suggestions if you need. It's one of my favorite steakhouses in the city.

Fantastic! Amazing! Delicious! 
The entire experience was wonderful. Had dinner with my Hubby to celebrate our Anniversary. This was our first time here & from Valet to end of meal everything was PERFECT! We had THE BEST SERVER, her name is Allegra! Please request her, you will not be disappointed. She is so wonderful, knowledgeable and pleasant. WE WILL BE VISITING AGAIN SOON. A special THANK YOU to everyone at Ocean Prime, you guys made our visit  so memorable, all of the staff, Mgrs, everyone greeted and checked in with us throughout the evening. The food and drinks were SO VERY GOOD. We ordered the Blackened Salmon, it was the most delicious & moist we've ever tasted. Dessert was a complimentary, we choose the ten layer Carrot cake. It was delicious. Beautiful atmosphere. Wonderful evening. 10s

The dine in experience is great . Check it out and enjoy! Good food, drinks and service as I stated before except it's even better in house!
Beautiful and serene ambiance.

I don't have anything good or bad to say about this place honestly... The vibe was nice  Pretty compact spot as it's located in center city in one of the busiest areas downtown. I'd suggest valet parking for my girls in heels... Save yourself the headache and request your car when you request the check also so that your vehicle is outside when you're ready to leave, to ensure that you're not standing outside in the cold. The clientele is all over the place--A little bit of everything going on in there. The drinks were delicious! But the food... Eh maybe I just ordered the wrong thing; I don't know. The crab cakes were horrible guys... I've eaten some of the best crab cakes in the world so I'm very hard to impress when it comes to this but I literally had to make sure I wasn't at a diner... because that's what it tasted like. The truffle Mac and the mashed were both very good but I still can't get over how unexciting those crab cakes were. I expected crab meat!! And it was some meat in there but more breading and filling than anything. I could've made better crab cakes myself. So I can't say I'll be back here, unless somebody I'm dining with suggest this place... Not impressed! And it's disappointing because I've always lived in Philly and wanted to give this place a try... Been there done that I guess!
